Set the base domain that new sites are created under when using the New Site command.<p>If sub-sites, type a domain of the form www.server.com. Sites are then created at www.server.com/siteName/.<p>If top-level sites are preferred, type a domain of the form .server.com. Sites are then created at siteName.server.com.<p>Note: for top-level sites, it's necessary to have a * DNS mapping for this domain pointing to this server.


